    "isi0" => "This simple tamarind vegetable can arouse your appetite. Various vegetables with a spicy and sour taste are guaranteed to make you devoured.<br><br>Vegetable tamarind or vegetable tamarind has many versions. There are clear ones with a typical Jakarta oncom blend. Or without oncom, Sundanese-style clear soup. There is also a Javanese tamarind vegetable which is spicy and has a slightly cloudy sauce.<br><br>The filling of vegetables can be chosen according to taste. Can be combined with young jackfruit, young jengkol, fresh red beans, and cabbage. Because vegetable tamarind is usually made from vegetables that are in the garden or easily available.</p>
    <p>If you're tempted to make tamarind vegetables, follow the recipe and tips below.</p>
    <p>Ingredients:<br>– 1 sweet corn, chopped<br>– 100 g young melinjo<br>– 2 cm galangal, crushed<br>– 2 bay leaves<br>– 1 chayote , chopped<br>– 5 long beans, chopped<br>– 50 g young melinjo leaves<br>– 3 young tamarind<br>– 1 small piece of palm sugar</p>
    <p><br>Seasoning:<br>– 8 pieces of curly red chili<br>– 5 pieces of red cayenne pepper<br>– 5 pieces of red onion<br>– 3 cloves of garlic<br>– 4 grains of candlenut< br>– 1 piece of grilled shrimp paste<br>– 2 tsp salt<br><br>How to make Sayur Asem Jawa:<br><br>Bring enough water in a saucepan, boil the corn and melinjo fruit until soft.<br>Inside separate pot, boil young tamarind with a little water until soft. Remove, knead, strain about 100 ml of water.<br>Seasoning: Grind or mash as you wish until smooth.<br>Put the spices and sugar into the corn stew, along with the galangal and bay leaf.<br>Add the chayote and long beans. Boil until soft.<br>Add melinjo leaves and young tamarind water, bring to a boil again.<br>Take it out and serve warm.</p>
    <p>SOURCE : https://food.detik.com/sayur/d-5577037/resep-sayur-asem-jawa-sederhana-yang-pedas-menyegarkan</p>",
