    'isi8' => '<p>Javanese acid is usually used for cooking, but who would have thought that Tamarind can also be made for very fresh ice.</p>
    <p>It has been a long time since people have known this drink as one of the culinary specialties of the archipelago. Usually, ES Asam Jawa is made at home. However, if you don`t have much time to make this drink, you can also find this drink in traditional markets and on the roadside.
    <p>To make your own tamarind ice at home, here`s how to make your own tamarind ice at home, which is reported from www.resepumiku.com</p>
    <h6>Recipe for Es Sari Tamarind Drink</h6>
    <h6>Ingredient of Tamarind Es Sari Drink </h6>
    <ul><li>200 grams of real tamarind</li><li>1 liter of water</li><li>sugar to taste</li></ul>
    <h6>How to Make Tamarind Es Sari Drink </h6>
    <ol><li>We first prepare the tamarind then clean it, and after that we cut it according to our taste</li><li>then turn on the stove over medium heat, prepare the pot and add the chopped tamarind into it, wait until the tamarind boils</li><li>after boiling we let it sit for about 7 minutes, reduce the stove heat</li><li>then take it out and let it cool for a while until it is really cold</li>< li>sieve the tamarind with a sieve and remove any remaining lumps</li><li>add some sugar</li><li>put it in the freezer</li><li>wait until frozen and ready to serve</li><li>Recipe for Javanese Tamarind Es Sari Drinks a la Nusantara</li></ol>
    <p>Well, that`s a very tasty and warm ice drink recipe, and there are many more, you know that are even tastier than the recipe above, you must be curious, good luck.</p>',
