    'isi9' => '<p>Selling Exports of Agricultural Products. Indonesian agricultural products have a lot of demand abroad. The proof is that many agricultural products are routinely exported with a fairly large nominal, even though the conditions are in decline.</p>
    <p>The Central Statistics Agency (BPS) noted that Indonesia`s total exports of agricultural products reached US$ 423.4 million. Down 8.61% compared to the previous month. In accumulated January-May 2015, exports were US$ 2.2 billion.</p>
    <p>Indonesia is a country that has the potential to export agricultural products with quality commodities. It is proven that the majority of the Indonesian population are farmers, both on farm and off farm farmers. According to BPS data, the number of Indonesian exports in agriculture on average has increased from year to year, although it sometimes fluctuates. Several commodities in Indonesia are very much demanded by importers from foreign countries to meet their country`s needs. It is undeniable that the quality of local commodities in Indonesia is unquestionable. The following is a list of commodities that are recognized by the world and have succeeded in printing as Indonesian export commodities.</p>
    <ol>
    <li><strong>Coffee</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>Indonesia is the largest coffee-producing country, as evidenced by the large number of coffee plantations in Indonesia with various characteristics that characterize the area. Coffee is a commodity that is forbidden if it can not be touched to the international market through exports. Rasa&nbsp;<a title="Indonesian coffee" href="https://www.agromaret.com/kopi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Indonesian coffee</a>&nbsp; both in the tongue of the Indonesian people themselves or the tongue of the world community. One of the country`s mainstay types of coffee is Kopi Luwak. This coffee, which is processed through the assistance of the civet animal, does have a unique characteristic both in terms of taste and process. Luwak coffee is much sought after by world coffee connoisseurs, considering that civet coffee only exists in Indonesia. Based on BPS data, coffee exports in 2015 amounted to 499,612.7 tons to 22 countries in the world.</p>
    <ol start="2">
    <li><strong>Tea</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>In addition to being suitable for the tongue of the Indonesian people, requests for&nbsp;<a title="teh" href="https://www.agromaret.com/teh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">teh&nbsp;< /a>the world continues to soar. According to BPS data, Indonesia`s export income data will increase in the 2000-2015 period, although in the 2013-2015 period, the income will decrease from 131,345.5 US$ to 89,630,2 US$</p>
    <ol start="3">
    <li><strong>Tobacco</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>Many people think that tobacco and cigarettes are the same thing, even though they have very different meanings. Tobacco is an agricultural crop and cigarettes are factory processed products. Tobacco can be used as a cold or flu medicine and the leaves can also be made into vegetables. Indonesia is one of the largest producers of tobacco commodities, so tobacco is included in the category of exporter commodities. According to BPS data, in 2015 Indonesia succeeded in exporting 11,574.2 tons of tobacco to 16 developed countries in the world.</p>
    <ol start="4">
    <li><strong>Chocolate Seeds</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>Chocolate beans or familiarly called cacao beans are one of the agricultural products in Indonesia which occupies the number three position of the largest cocoa producer in the world. Cocoa beans can be made in various variants of chocolate flavors which are very delicious and suitable to be used as a mainstay product. Unfortunately, cocoa exports are still in the form of results&nbsp;<em>on farm</em>&nbsp;not&nbsp;<em>off farm</em>. Currently, cocoa bean processing producers are increasingly being developed. Even so, the quality of off farm produce is still unable to compete with foreign processed products such as Belgium. Statistical data shows exports of cocoa beans amounted to 55,299.4 tons with an income of US$ 118,282.5. This figure should be a matter of pride and a challenge for Indonesia to develop cocoa bean processing in a form and attractiveness that is able to align with foreign products.</p>
    <ol start="5">
    <li><strong>Fruits</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>Another export quality agricultural product is fruit. Indeed, technologically, Indonesia is still less competitive with technology in several developed countries. However, it is undeniable that Indonesia has added value in terms of fruit productivity considering its land and geographical area bonuses. Some of the fruits that become mainstay commodities are mangosteen, soursop, and guava. These three fruits have dominated the international market, so many farmers are competing to improve the quality of fruits in Indonesia.</p>
    <ol start="6">
    <li><strong>Rubber</strong></li>',
