    'isi12' => '<h6 style="background: white;"><span style="color: #404040; font-weight: normal;">Agroforestry, Climate and Crop Distributors</span></h6>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Plant Distributors. In agricultural products agroforestry, trees are raised as a source of wood, pulp, or fuel. In many areas, this kind of intensive forestry is being developed as an alternative to harvesting natural forest.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">In temperate climates, the most important trees planted are pine, spruce, larch, and poplars. Depending on species and site conditions, these trees can be harvested after a growth period of only 10 to 60 years, compared to 60 to more than 100 years for natural, managed forests in the same area.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">In the tropics, fast-growing, high-yielding species of trees are grown for use locally as fuel , animal feed, wood, and pulpwood. Various tree species include pine, eucalyptus dia-oak, and tree-nut. Slowergrowing tropical hardwoods, such as teak and mahogany, are grown for their high quality wood.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Climate dominates agriculture, second only to irrigation. Plants are very susceptible to weather variations, such as late or early snow, heavy rain, or drought. Because of their ability to grow in a wide range of climates, rice, wheat and corn have become the dominant crops globally.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">These plants all need a rainy season for germination and growth, followed by a dry season to allow rot free storage . Rice is domesticated in the seasonal soils of Southeast Asia, while wheat comes from the Fertile Crescent of the Middle East. Historically, wheat was planted in the fall and harvested in late spring, coinciding with the cycles of wet and dry seasons in the Mediterranean region. Corn needs the heavy summer rain provided by Mexico`s highland climate.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Another plant common in areas with less favorable climates. These include barley on semiarid lands (those with light rainfall); wheat and potatoes in cool, moist soil; rye in cold climates with a short growing season; and dry rice on hillsides and dry land.</span></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Although food production is the main emphasis in agriculture, more and more industrial applications have evolved. Fabric fibers, such as cotton, have been the mainstay, but paper products and chemicals now come from cultivated plants.</span></p>
