    'isi13' => '<p>Selling and Buying Agricultural Commodity Products. In agricultural products&nbsp;<a title="Agriculture" href="https://asamjawagunung.com/">agriculture&nbsp;</a><b>cultivation</b>&nbsp;is a planned maintenance activity&nbsp;<a class= "mw-redirect" title="Biological resources" href="https://asamjawagunung.com/">biological resources</a>&nbsp;which is carried out on an area of ​​land for harvesting benefits/products. Cultivation activities can be considered as the core of&nbsp;<a class="mw-redirect" title="Farming business" href="https://asamjawagunung.com/">farming business</a>. According to the Big Indonesian Dictionary, cultivation is “a useful and fruitful endeavor.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"></sup></p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Cultivation refers to the farming of aquatic animals and plants for use as food. Increasingly, aquaculture or fish farming is seen as an alternative to the exploitation of wild species of aquatic animals and plants.</span></p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Most freshwater aquaculture occurs in inland areas where there are many ponds and small lakes. Freshwater aquaculture is especially important in Asia, where a wide variety of fish, especially carp and tilapia, are raised in artificial ponds. In North America, the most common species of fish growing in small ponds are rainbow trout and catfish.</span></p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: .25in; background: white;"><span style="color: #404040;">Aquaculture is also becoming increasingly important along marine protected coastlines in many parts of the world. In the tropics, large areas of mangrove forest are being converted into shallow ponds for shrimp farming. In North America and Western Europe, Atlantic salmon farming became a widespread industry in the late twentieth century, using pens floating in shallow, coastal bays and occasionally in the open ocean.
